The agent A provided the following violation scenario:In the metal_log call inside the if (result < 0) branch the format string has a single "%s" but two arguments are supplied: ldev->dev_path and strerror(-result). The call to strerror(-result) is evaluated but not used by the format string, so that evaluation is unnecessary (dead code) — removing it would not change the program behaviour (aside from any implementation-specific side effects of strerror). Additionally, the mismatched format/arguments can cause undefined behaviour for a printf-like variadic call.
</scenario>
